text: Cats sleep 70% of their lives.
Cats have five toes on their front paws and four on the back.
A group of cats is called a clowder.
Cats can rotate their ears 180 degrees.
A cat can jump up to six times its length.
Cats have whiskers on the backs of their front legs.
Adult cats only meow to communicate with humans.
Cats can make over 100 different sounds.
A cat’s nose has a unique pattern like a human fingerprint.
Cats have a third eyelid called the haw.
Cats can run up to 30 miles per hour.
Cats sweat through their paws.
The oldest known pet cat was found in a 9,500-year-old grave.
Cats’ purring may have healing properties.
Some cats are allergic to humans.
Cats have free-floating clavicle bones, which allow them to squeeze through tight spaces.
Cats can’t taste sweetness.
Kneading is a leftover kitten behavior used for nursing.
Cats have been domesticated for over 4,000 years.
The first cloned pet was a cat named 'CC'.
Cats can see in near darkness.
The average cat sleeps 12–16 hours a day.
Cats groom themselves to regulate body temperature.
The heaviest domestic cat on record weighed over 21 kg.
Cats can hear ultrasonic sounds.
Some cats enjoy swimming.
A cat's brain is 90% similar to a human’s brain.
Cats can dream during REM sleep.
Polydactyl cats have extra toes.
A cat’s heart beats nearly twice as fast as a human’s.
Cats rub against people to mark territory with scent glands.
Cats have a unique walking pattern: both right feet move together, then both left feet.
The largest breed of domestic cat is the Maine Coon.
Cats are known to reduce stress in humans.
Some cats can be trained to walk on a leash.
Cats’ whiskers are touch-sensitive hairs called vibrissae.
Cats can recognize their own name.
Cats’ pupils expand and contract to control light intake.
The oldest living cat on record lived to be 38 years old.
Cats communicate using body language, vocalizations, and scent markings.
Cats purr when they are happy, stressed, or in pain.
Cats’ hearing is better than dogs, especially at higher frequencies.
Cats can rotate their ears independently to detect the direction of sound.
Cats’ grooming helps prevent infections and parasites.
Cats have a strong hunting instinct and often bring 'gifts' to owners.
Cats can be lactose intolerant.
Cats blink slowly to show trust and affection.
Cats have a sensitive sense of smell, much stronger than humans.
Cats can become addicted to catnip.
Cats can survive falls from high places due to their righting reflex.
Cats mark territory with scent glands located on their face, paws, and tail.
